You can test your webhook in the Stripe Dashboard:

1. Go to: https://dashboard.stripe.com/webhooks
2. Click on your webhook endpoint
3. Click "Send test webhook" button
4. Select an event type (e.g., `checkout.session.completed`)
5. Click "Send test webhook"
6. Check your server logs to see if the event was received and processed

## Method 2: Test via Stripe CLI (if authenticated)

If you have Stripe CLI authenticated, you can trigger test events:

```bash
# Test checkout completion
stripe trigger checkout.session.completed

# Test subscription creation
stripe trigger customer.subscription.created

# Test payment success
stripe trigger invoice.payment_succeeded
```

## Method 3: Manual End-to-End Test

1. **Start your dev server** (if not running):
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```

2. **Go to your app** and log in

3. **Click "Fin Pro"** in the chat dropdown menu

4. **Select a plan** (Weekly or Monthly) on the upgrade page

5. **Click "Upgrade to Pro"** - this will redirect to Stripe Checkout

6. **Use Stripe test card**: `4242 4242 4242 4242` (any future expiry, any CVC)

7. **Complete the checkout** - this will trigger the webhook

8. **Check your server logs** to see webhook processing

9. **Verify in database** - check if subscription was created in `user_subscriptions` table

## What to Look For

âœ… **Success indicators:**
- Webhook receives 200 response
- No errors in server logs
- Subscription record created/updated in database
- User sees "Manage Subscription" instead of "Fin Pro" in dropdown

âŒ **Failure indicators:**
- 400/401 errors (signature verification failed)
- 500 errors (webhook processing failed)
- No database record created
- Errors in server console

Let me know what you see when testing!


